[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzer run on the codebase triggered a critical security alert for a remote JNDI [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup. During log message processing, an attacker-controlled JNDI URL was passed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough Log4j’s variable substitution mechanism. This lookup was intercepted by [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJazzer’s `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook`, which raised a [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception, indicating a potential remote code [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution or data exfiltration vulnerability.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Description  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer input caused the application’s logging subsystem [0m[1;39m([0m[39mApache Log4j[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperform a JNDI lookup on a remote URL supplied by the attacker. Jazzer detected and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocked this lookup, throwing [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI Lookup`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSuch remote JNDI lookups are known to enable either arbitrary code execution on the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhost or the leaking of sensitive information, depending on the JDK version and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup target.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Remote JNDI Lookup leading to potential remote code execution or information [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexfiltration.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations and Findings  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The exception originates in `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJazzer [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at line [0m[1;36m61[0m[39m.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The lookup is invoked by [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Log4j’s `StrSubstitutor` and `PatternLayout` classes are performing variable [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolution on log messages, ultimately calling `JndiLookup`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. The stack trace reaches the user’s fuzzer harness at [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`, confirming the log message content [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginated from the fuzzing input.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup`: how it parses and executes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNDI URLs.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.Interpolator` and `StrSubstitutor`: the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubstitution logic that invokes lookups.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m:     * Get the value of the JNDI resource.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:     * @param key  the JNDI resource name to be looked up, may be null[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m:     * @return The value of the JNDI resource.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcore/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/Interpolator.jav[0m[1;92ma:62[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:    public [0m[1;35mInterpolator[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:        this.defaultLookup = new [0m[1;35mMapLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew HashMap<String, String>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"sys"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mSystemPropertiesLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"env"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mEnvironmentLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Summary of the root cause  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The codebase’s default logging configuration unconditionally registers and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvokes the “jndi:” [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link StrLookup[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the Interpolator, with a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhard-coded static flag [0m[33mENABLE_JNDI[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m. As a result, attacker-controlled [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjndi:ldap:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m…[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m” patterns in log messages trigger a remote JNDI lookup at format [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtime, leading to potential RCE or data exfiltration.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Overall remediation approach  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   We must disable remote “jndi:” lookups by default in all out-of-the-box Log4j [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatternLayouts, while preserving the ability for advanced users to opt back in if [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey have a safe, local JNDI environment. Concretely, we will:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Turn off JNDI lookups by default at class-load time [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstatic flag = false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Expose a new documented system property [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. “log4j2.enableJndiLookup”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat, if set to true, re-enables JNDI lookups.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Update both JndiLookup and the Interpolator registration logic to respect [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis flag.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Keep all other variable lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39menv, sys, map, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m untouched.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed patch steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Change the static ENABLE_JNDI field to be initialized from a system [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty:  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        – private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI = [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mBoolean.getBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Remove any default true assignment. Document in the Javadoc that users may [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset -Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndiLookup[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m to re-enable.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Provide a public static [0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m accessor for use elsewhere. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Leave [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mevent, key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m logic unchanged apart from the new ENABLE_JNDI [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag check.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.Interpolator [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno-arg constructor[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Change:  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to:  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • This ensures JndiLookup is not even registered when the flag is false, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoiding any unintended calls.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Add Javadoc and release notes  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Document the new system property “log4j2.enableJndiLookup” in the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mConfiguration and Lookups user guide.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Explain the security rationale and note that JNDI lookups are disabled by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault in this version.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why this approach is optimal  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Security-by-default: disables the dangerous feature for all users, closing the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlog4shell vector.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Opt-in: advanced users with a secure JNDI environment can restore [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality via a documented property; no code changes needed.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Minimal surface: only touches JndiLookup and the Interpolator registration; [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall other lookups remain intact.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Non-breaking for users who do not rely on JNDI lookups. Only those who [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepended on remote JNDI must explicitly opt in.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No changes to harness, tests, or external dependencies. Existing tests for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menvironment and system-property lookups continue to pass.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Preservation of existing logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – When “-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndiLookup[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m” is provided, ENABLE_JNDI becomes true, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInterpolator registers JndiLookup, and [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mevent, key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m behaves exactly as [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – All non-JNDI lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“sys:”, “env:”, default variables[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain unaffected.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – PatternLayout, StrSubstitutor, MessagePatternConverter, and the entire [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatting pipeline remain unchanged except for the absence of the “jndi” lookup.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Side effect: legitimate JNDI resource lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., container resources[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe disabled unless users opt in.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Mitigation: clearly document the property in the migration guide and user [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanual; tests for JNDI lookups should be updated [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif any exist[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to set the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mre-enable system property.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. References to analogous fixes  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – This mirrors Log4j [0m[1;36m2.15[0m[39m.[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m’s “disable lookups by default” change for mitigating[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlog4shell.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Similar system-property flags exist elsewhere in Log4j [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatMsgNoLookups[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, following the same pattern.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCode ranges to be modified:  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.jav[0m[1;92ma[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m:31[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m39[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/Interpolator.ja[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mv[0m[1;92ma:62[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run flagged a critical security issue in Apache Log4j Core: an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munguarded JNDI lookup [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`JndiLookup.lookup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that can be driven by [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled input, leading to remote code execution or data exfiltration. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn response, a patch was proposed that:  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Replaces the mutable `ENABLE_JNDI` flag in JndiLookup.java with a `static final [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean` driven by the system property `log4j2.enableJndiLookup`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds an `[0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` accessor in JndiLookup.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modifies Interpolator.java to register the “jndi” lookup only when [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns true.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying these changes, the build failed in the core module with a [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation error:  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“cannot assign a value to final variable ENABLE_JNDI” at `JndiLookup.jav[0m[1;92ma:94[0m[39m`.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Jazzer reported:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLookup`  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace highlights that [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minvoked via [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Interpolator` → `StrSubstitutor` → logging appenders[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m performs a JNDI lookup on [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled data.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Entry point is a fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe core of the issue is the unguarded JNDI invocation in the logging library.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **In JndiLookup.java**  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     *Original*  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     *Patched*  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - Change to  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI = [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mBoolean.getBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - Add Javadoc explaining the new system-property override.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - Add a public `static boolean [0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that returns `ENABLE_JNDI`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **In Interpolator.java**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     *Original*  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     *Patched*  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Application Result**  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maven compilation failed in `log4j-core` with:  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m…[0m[35m/[0m[95mJndiLookup.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m94[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m9[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cannot assign a value to final variable [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mENABLE_JNDI  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The reactor summary shows all other modules succeeded and only the core module[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation failed.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error indicates that somewhere in the modified `JndiLookup.java` the code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill attempts to assign to `ENABLE_JNDI`, which is now declared `final`.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **JndiLookup.java**  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Review line [0m[1;36m94[0m[39m and surrounding code to locate any assignments to [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Confirm that `ENABLE_JNDI` is never reassigned after its `final` [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Interpolator.java**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Verify that conditional registration of the “jndi” lookup behaves as [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended and that no other code path reinstates JndiLookup unconditionally.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Other Lookup Implementations**  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Audit all built-in lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `StrSubstitutor`, `PatternLayout`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure no other code paths invoke JNDI without the guard.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Build and Test Infrastructure**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Check for any tests or static initializers that might set or override [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI` at runtime or attempt to reassign it.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Ensure the system property mechanism [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mBoolean.getBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdocumented and validated by integration tests.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Fix the ENABLE_JNDI field in JndiLookup.java  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change its declaration to a single `static final` field initialized from the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystem property:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Before[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * Controls whether JNDI lookups are enabled. Default is false; set[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * -Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndiLookup[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m to allow.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI =[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mBoolean.getBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Keep only one public accessor:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return ENABLE_JNDI;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. **Remove** the old mutator and legacy getter entirely:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public static void [0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean enableJndi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;33mDELETE[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m                 [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;33mDELETE[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Rationale: a `final` field can’t be reassigned. Removing the setter [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutdated getter[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m eliminates the compile error “cannot assign a value to final [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariable ENABLE_JNDI” and enforces a secure, immutable guard.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Guard JNDI registration in Interpolator.java  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In the default constructor, replace the unconditional lookup registration:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Before[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This change means that unless `-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndiLookup[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m` is explicitly [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset, no JNDI lookup plugin is registered and attacker-controlled inputs cannot [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreach `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Audit for residual ENABLE_JNDI assignments and legacy API calls  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Search the core module for `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and remove or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdate them to use `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm no other code paths or static initializers attempt to reassign [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mENABLE_JNDI.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve existing tests and harnesses  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because system-property usage is transparent to client code, existing tests [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the fuzzing harness will see JNDI lookups disabled by default.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No test code or harness modifications are required.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Verification  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the entire project; the compilation error in log4j-core should [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisappear.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run unit and integration tests to ensure no breakage.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execute the original Jazzer fuzz target: verify that without the system [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty, `Interpolator` no longer registers “jndi” and the fuzzer no longer flags [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma JNDI lookup.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhy this is optimal:  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It directly addresses the compilation failure by removing illegal assignment to a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`final` field.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It preserves all existing logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe JNDI lookup code remains intact, only its [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregistration is guarded[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It enforces secure defaults: disabling JNDI lookups unless explicitly enabled.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It avoids any changes to harness or test code, maintaining backward compatibility[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith existing tests.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar conditional-registration patterns already exist for other lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“env”, “sys”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so this follows established codebase conventions.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effects are minimal: clients that depend on JNDI lookups must now [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpass the system property flag, which is documented in Javadoc.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception due to remote JNDI lookups in Log4j’s [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`JndiLookup`, exposing potential remote code execution or data exfiltration.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patch attempt: Modified `JndiLookup` to disable lookups by default [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontrolled [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia `log4j2.enableJndiLookup` system property[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, removed legacy setter/getter [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`setEnableJndi`, `isEnableJndi`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, added a new `[0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method; updated [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Interpolator` to only register the “jndi” lookup when enabled.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patch result: Build failures in core tests. Multiple test classes still call the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoved `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, causing compilation errors.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzer invocation in `SimpleLoggerFuzzer` leads to a stack trace involving [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` and Log4j’s `JndiLookup`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The exception indicates a security finding: attacker-controlled remote JNDI [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookups can lead to RCE or information leaks.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash is reproducible via a libFuzzer input, implying the codebase lacks [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madequate JNDI lookup safeguards.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key observations in the issue  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability arises in `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests and application code rely on enabling/disabling JNDI lookups at runtime [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia public setters/getters.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness triggers a warning path in the logging framework that [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mactivates JNDI resolution.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         An automated security test [1m([0mvia Jazzer[1m)[0m triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exception pointing to a remote JNDI lookup vulnerability in Log4j’s `JndiLookup`.   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         In response, a patch was proposed that removes the legacy `setEnableJndi` and       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `isEnableJndi` methods from `JndiLookup` and updates references in several test     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         classes to use a non-existent `[1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method instead. After applying the      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patch, the build fails with compilation errors in four test files, all complaining  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that `[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` cannot be found.                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - A Jazzer fuzzer invocation caused a critical security alert:                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Lookup`                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The stack trace shows that `[1;35mNamingContextLookup.lookupHook[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` were invoked during pattern substitution in Log4j [1m([0mvia        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Interpolator`, `StrSubstitutor`, `PatternLayout`, etc.[1m)[0m.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The core concern is that attacker-controlled JNDI URLs can lead to remote code    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execution or data exfiltration.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - In `JndiLookup.java`, the methods                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           ```java                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           public static void [1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1m([0mboolean enableJndi[1m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           public static boolean [1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           ```                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           were removed with the comment “Legacy setter and getter methods removed. Use      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m instead.”                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - In four test classes —                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           `JndiLookupTest.java`, `InterpolatorTest.java`,                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `RoutingAppenderWithJndiTest.java` —                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           occurrences of `[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` were replaced by                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Result                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Maven compilation of `log4j-core` fails during test compilation:                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           ```                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           cannot find symbol: method [1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           location: class org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           ```                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The errors occur in:                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - RoutingAppenderWithJndiTest.java [1m([0mline [1;36m93[0m[1m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - JndiLookupTest.java [1m([0mline [1;36m53[0m[1m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - InterpolatorTest.java [1m([0mlines [1;36m65[0m and [1;36m89[0m[1m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - No `[1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method exists in `JndiLookup`, so all references in tests are    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         unresolved.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Areas for Further Investigation                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The current `JndiLookup` API: confirm whether an `[1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method is defined  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or intended to exist.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The commit history or documentation that introduced `[1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` as a            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         replacement, to locate its definition or spec.                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - All usages of `ENABLE_JNDI`, `setEnableJndi`, and `isEnableJndi` across the       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         codebase [1m([0mnot only in tests[1m)[0m to ensure consistency.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The security sanitizer hook in `NamingContextLookup` and any configuration flags  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         controlling JNDI lookups.                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Investigate JndiLookup.java to confirm the existence and mutability of the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal `ENABLE_JNDI` flag.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure that `ENABLE_JNDI` is declared as a non-final `static boolean`, so both[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msetter and getter can modify/read it.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This field is the single source of truth for whether JNDI lookups are [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpermitted.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Reintroduce a new, public `[0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method and an accompanying [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msetEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method in `JndiLookup.java`, mapping directly to the existing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI` flag:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Insert immediately after [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor near[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the existing `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * Returns whether JNDI lookups are enabled.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * @return true if JNDI lookups are enabled.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * @since [0m[1;36m2.[0m[39mx[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return ENABLE_JNDI;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * Enables or disables JNDI lookups.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * @param enabled true to enable JNDI lookups.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * @since [0m[1;36m2.[0m[39mx[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public static void [0m[1;35msetEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal boolean enabled[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ENABLE_JNDI = enabled;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not remove or alter the legacy `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods; leave them for backward compatibility.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Leave the test code references to `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` unchanged.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing test patch already replaced calls to `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. With the new methods in place, the tests will now compile and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserve their original guard behavior.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No further edits to test files are required.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Retain all other logic in `JndiLookup`, including security sanitation via [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mNamingContextLookup.lookupHook[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, unchanged to avoid regressions in core [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Validate the patch:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild `log4j-core` to ensure no compilation errors.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the full test suite to confirm that all JNDI-related tests execute [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly when `ENABLE_JNDI` is true, and short‐circuit when false.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run Jazzer fuzzer to verify that the remote JNDI lookup vulnerability [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains mitigated under the new configuration API.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introducing `[0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` directly addresses the compilation failures in the four[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtest classes without touching harness code or external libraries.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By mapping both legacy and new methods to the same `ENABLE_JNDI` flag, we [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserve existing functionality and guard conditions in tests.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This solution is minimal, low-risk, and aligns with the intended API change [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“Use[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m instead”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, satisfying the test updates and avoiding breakage of [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munrelated components.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
