[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a security finding raised by Jazzer indicating a “Remote JNDI  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Lookup” via Log4j’s JndiLookup.lookup method, which can lead to remote code         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execution or data exfiltration. A patch was applied to the `JndiLookup` class,      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         introducing public methods `[1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and `[1;35msetEnabled[0m[1m([0mboolean[1m)[0m` to control the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ENABLE_JNDI` flag. After applying this patch, the fuzzer still triggers the same   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI Lookup` exception with an identical stack [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         trace, indicating that JNDI lookups remain enabled and that the patch did not       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         suppress or alter the vulnerable behavior.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer fuzzer run produced a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` error citing a    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         “Remote JNDI Lookup.”                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace highlights a call chain starting in                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook`, proceeding into                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup`, and continuing through    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Log4j’s lookup and formatting machinery [1m([0m`Interpolator`, `StrSubstitutor`,          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `PatternLayout`, etc.[1m)[0m.                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The finding notes that attacker-controlled remote JNDI URLs may lead to code   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execution or information leakage.                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important Observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The exception is flagged by                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.NamingContextLookup.lookupHook`.           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The vulnerable call originates in `JndiLookup.lookup` at line [1;36m60[0m of            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup.java`.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The rest of the trace shows normal logging pipeline activity, confirming that  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the vulnerability is triggered during message substitution.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File modified:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.java`           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Additions:                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```java                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              public static boolean [1;35misEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  return ENABLE_JNDI;                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              public static void [1;35msetEnabled[0m[1m([0mfinal boolean enabled[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  ENABLE_JNDI = enabled;                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - These methods are appended after the existing `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method,         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         providing a setter to toggle the `ENABLE_JNDI` flag at runtime.                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Result After Patch                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Re-running the fuzzer yields the same `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JNDI Lookup` exception.                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace is unchanged, indicating that JNDI lookups remain active and   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the newly introduced setter logic is not exercised by the current harness or        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         default configuration.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Further Investigation                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Examine the declaration and initialization of `ENABLE_JNDI` in                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup.java`—is it a compile-time constant or bound to an                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         environment/property?                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review the code path in `JndiLookup.lookup` to see whether it checks           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ENABLE_JNDI` before performing lookups.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Inspect `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` to understand how and when it         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         intercepts JNDI calls.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Trace configuration loading for Log4j [1m([0msystem properties, environment          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         variables[1m)[0m to see how `ENABLE_JNDI` is intended to be toggled.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Audit other lookup classes [1m([0me.g., `JdbcLookup`, `LDAPLookup`[1m)[0m for similar      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patterns or flags that control remote resource access.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m** JNDI resourcce path prefix used in a J2EE container *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:    static final String CONTAINER_JNDI_RESOURCE_PATH_PREFIX = [0m[32m"java:comp/env/"[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Root Cause Analysis**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `JndiLookup` class uses a hard-coded static boolean `ENABLE_JNDI = true` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat never changes unless the new setter is explicitly called.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No code path in Log4j or the fuzzer harness invokes [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, so the guard `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!ENABLE_JNDI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return null;` is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnever exercised.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - As a result, remote JNDI lookups remain enabled by default and continue to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrigger the Jazzer security sanitizer.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Overall Approach**  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Initialize `ENABLE_JNDI` from a well-known configuration [0m[1;39m([0m[39msystem property or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLog4j configuration[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at class load time rather than hard-coding it to `true`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use Log4j’s `PropertiesUtil` to read a boolean property named something like [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Choose a secure default of `false` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJNDI disabled[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to mitigate the [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability out of the box, while allowing users to re-enable it explicitly if [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeded.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Preserve the public setter and getter so that dynamic toggling remains [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpossible for advanced use cases or tests.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Detailed Patch Steps**  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. **Import the configuration utility**  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Add:  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        import org.apache.logging.log4j.util.PropertiesUtil;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This provides access to system and configuration properties in a uniform [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mway.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. **Define a constant for the property name**  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Immediately after the class declaration [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor at the top of the field block[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd:  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private static final String ENABLE_JNDI_PROPERTY = [0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. **Change the static initialization of `ENABLE_JNDI`**  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace the existing line:  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - With code that reads the property, defaulting to `false`:  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI =[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mPropertiesUtil.getProperties[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          [0m[1;35m.getBooleanProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[39mENABLE_JNDI_PROPERTY, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. **Retain the setter and getter**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Keep the previously added methods:  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return ENABLE_JNDI; [0m[1;39m}[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public static void [0m[1;35msetEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal boolean enabled[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            ENABLE_JNDI = enabled;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This ensures existing tests or code that manually toggles JNDI continue to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction correctly.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. **Update Javadoc/comment**  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In the class or above the property definition, document the new system [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty:  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * Controls whether remote JNDI lookups are allowed.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * System property: [0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault = false[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Justification & Benefits**  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By reading from a configurable property, we can disable JNDI lookups by [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault, immediately mitigating the fuzzer-detected vulnerability without removing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Users who rely on JNDI can still enable it at startup with [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndi[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m` or programmatically via `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The guard in `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` remains intact, so when disabled, all calls return [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`null` before instantiating any `InitialContext`.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Preservation of Existing Logic**  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The only behavioral change for users who do not set the property is that JNDI [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookups are disabled.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sequence of checks and the format‐substitution mechanism in [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Interpolator`, `StrSubstitutor`, and `PatternLayout` are untouched.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No fuzzing harness or test code is modified; the same `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI is in place with an additional configuration hook.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Potential Side Effects & Mitigations**  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Backward Compatibility: Applications expecting JNDI lookups at runtime will [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow get `null` unless they explicitly enable the feature.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     *Mitigation:* Clearly document the new default behavior and the property to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mre-enable JNDI.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Performance: A tiny one-time lookup of a system property at class load; [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegligible impact.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Race Conditions: The setter may be called after the class is initialized; this[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinues to work as before.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **References & Similar Patterns**  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other lookup classes in Log4j [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `JdbcLookup`, `JndiManager` in later [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mversions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m use `PropertiesUtil` to read configuration flags at startup.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Apache Log4j [0m[1;36m2.15[0m[39m+ adopted this exact pattern for disabling JNDI by default: [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading from `log4j2.enableJndi`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. **No Harness or Test Code Changes**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not touch any fuzzing harness, test files, or external libraries. All [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanges are local to `JndiLookup.java`.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCode context for patch:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.jav[0m[1;92ma[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m:29[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m37[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.jav[0m[1;92ma[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m:31[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
